title: How To | No Makeup Look
description:
The trick to a natural ‘no makeup’ look, use a foundation with light coverage and opt for natural colors on your lips and eyes. 

Step 1: Start with a light foundation.

Step 2: Apply a highlight powder, like Neutrogena Healthy Skin® Blush in Luminous, all over face. Focusing most on the cheekbone area and eye creases.

Step 3: Use natural eye shadow tones on eyes.

Step 4: Finish look with a peachy-pink color on lips. 

Now you have a no makeup look for those natural kind of days. Follow our ‘How To’ series for more everyday makeup tips!

transcripts: The key to getting a subtle no make up look is to use a foundation with light coverage and use natural colors on your lips and eyes. Start with a light foundation. I'm using Neutrogena liquid skin liquid make up. Now I'm just going to apply the Neutrogena highlight powder all over my face focusing more on my cheek bone area and the creases of my eyes. I'm going to be using the nourishing  long wear eye shadow in classic nude. First I'm going to apply the peach color all over my eye lid. Then using the taupe shade, I'm going to apply this right into the crease and lastly, using the eggshell nude color, I'm going to highlight right underneath my brows. As a from of eye liner, I'll be using the espresso brown color on my upper lash line. To finish the look I'll use the moisture smooth color stick and fresh papaya. Then I'm just going to wipe off any excess with my fingertip. And there you have it; a natural look for those make up kind of days.
